                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12742424" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2009 17:03:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Given our goal is to turn around Solr 1.4 fairly quickly after 2.9 and the fact that this issue doesn&apos;t have a patch, should we mark it as 1.5?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12742425" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2009 17:05:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Depends on how quickly we can get it in.&lt;br/&gt;
I hate to see good functionality put in Lucene that can&apos;t be used in Solr, and this should help us (and others) debug any fieldcache issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12742428" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2009 17:09:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah - I&apos;d wait to push this - its an easy one to push last second if we have to. 2.9 is not out yet, and if a good patch is up soon - why not put it in?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its important here for similar reasons that its important to get in Lucene 2.9.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d been waiting for the issue to get committed to start (it relies on functionality in Lucene that is not there in Solr yet)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But really there is no need to wait - I had just started thinking about the best way to go about it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12742437" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2009 17:29:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, definitely agree, was just going through the 1.4 unresolved list and this one had no progress, so I thought I would ask.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12752949" author="hossman" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 07:45:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;rough start ... adds a hardcoded MBean that just wraps FieldCache.getEntries() and FieldCacheSanityChecker in it&apos;s getStatistics() method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12752952" author="hossman" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 07:49:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;this does everything the issue summary suggests in a very simple way ... but personally i think we should also use FieldCache.setInfoStream and and log an error anytime anything is written to that stream &amp;#8211; but i&apos;m not sure if it&apos;s worth adding an option for that ... if it was always on it could (concievably) have a noticeable effect on static warming of many small field caches. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12753252" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 21:44:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this include the memory size of UnInvertedField?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12753316" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 23:55:20 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Does this include the memory size of UnInvertedField?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;UnInvertedField already did it&apos;s own size calculation (along with other stats about number of terms).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12753346" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2009 01:32:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I did an open call hierarchy on UnInvertedField.memSize, which is called by toString which isn&apos;t called by anything so I assume it never makes it to the web UI?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12754188" author="gsingers" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2009 17:10:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a reasonable first pass, Hoss.  I think we should commit and then we can iterate in 1.5.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12759243" author="hossman" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 21:36:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like as far as we&apos;ll get on this for 1.4...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 818618.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12759410" author="shalinmangar" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2009 08:01:54 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I did an open call hierarchy on UnInvertedField.memSize, which is called by toString which isn&apos;t called by anything so I assume it never makes it to the web UI?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jason is right. The UninvertedField&apos;s memSize never shows up on the statistics page. I&apos;ll open another issue to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12759419" author="shalinmangar" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2009 08:32:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1461&quot; title=&quot;Expose UnInvertedField&amp;#39;s memory usage in statistics page&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1461&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1461&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767482" author="hossman" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 20:45:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Followup note...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hossman@brunner:~/lucene/solr$ svn commit -m &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1292&quot; title=&quot;show lucene fieldcache entries and sizes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1292&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1292&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: followup tweak based on mailing list discussion: for indexes with lots of segments, estimating the size of all the field caches can take a lot of time (particularly with lots of String based caches) so for now we only estimate the size for items which are part of instanity instances&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
Sending        src/java/org/apache/solr/search/SolrFieldCacheMBean.java&lt;br/&gt;
Transmitting file data .&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 826788.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775812" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:52:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
